        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 4:36PM EDT until June 27 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>SVRRAH

The National Weather Service in Raleigh has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Western Moore County in central North Carolina...
Southeastern Montgomery County in central North Carolina...
Northwestern Hoke County in central North Carolina...

* Until 515 PM EDT.

* At 434 PM EDT, a cluster of severe thunderstorms were located from
near Pinehurst to Robbins to near Troy, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Southern Pines, Pinehurst, Aberdeen, Biscoe, Whispering Pines,
Pinebluff, Robbins, Foxfire, Candor, and Taylortown.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with this storm. Move indoors immediately. Lightning is
one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder,
you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
